 <H1>Formal Relational Query Languages</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<H2>Two mathematical Query Languages form the basis for “real” languages (e.g. SQL), and for implementation:
</H2>
<BR></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Relational Algebra:  More operational, very useful for representing execution plans.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Relational Calculus:   Lets users describe what they want, rather than how to compute it.  (Non-operational, declarative.)
</H2>
</UL></P>
<P><UL>
<LI>  Understanding Algebra & Calculus is key to 
</UL><UL>
<LI>  understanding SQL, query processing! </UL></P>
